Commentary: Asghar returns and takes down Ervine. He celebrates the wicket with a fist pump. Sammy is pumped too. Poor shot from Ervine. He backs away outside leg, exposing his stumps. Then looks to cut a ball that isn't really short. Looks to cut against the spin. Eventually, he does not make contact. The ball skids on and it's timbaaah

Commentary: stumping chance sent upstairs. Tossed up and drifts away outside off, drags Nawaz forward and goes past the outside edge. Kamran collects the ball and takes the bails off. Nawaz loses his balance and lifts his back leg. Seems like the foot is on the line by the time the bails come off. Tough one for Raza, the TV umpire. Out is the verdict. Two wickets in two balls, Peshawar are closing in on the title
Commentary_short: Mohammad Asghar to Mohammad Nawaz, OUT

Commentary: Peshawar Zalmi are the champions of the second season of the PSL! The fireworks go off, and Sammy calls his boys for the selfie celebration. Then every Peshawar player attempts the Afridi star-man pose. The crowd goes berserk. Well done, Peshawar. They rejoice further. It was Hasan who set it up with the new ball and sealed it with the old one. This was full and right on the off stump. Babar looks to slug it away across the line. He only connects with a whole lot of thin air. The off stump is tilted back
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Zulfiqar Babar, OUT
